-# Playbook 01: Financial Analysis
-
-Covers definitions, purchase price mechanics, funds flow, escrows, and true-up.
-
-**REQUIREMENT:** Do not produce Definition Analysis unless `/mnt/data/definitions.jsonl` exists and is loaded for this exact document. Reuse it if it already exists; otherwise create it by following `extract-terms.md`.
-
----
-
-## When to Use
-
-- User asks about definitions (Indebtedness, Cash, Working Capital, Transaction Expenses)
-- User asks about purchase price, price bridge, adjustments, funds flow
-- User mentions double-counting, overlap, bucket placement
-- User asks about escrow, holdback, true-up, closing statement
-- User asks about dispute resolution, independent accountant
-
----
-
-## Output Contract (strict)
-
-Default interaction model:
-
-- Start with the **Definition Analysis** below (default; definitions-only).
-- Ask at most **one** clarifying question. If unclear, do the Definition Analysis.
-- End every response with a short **Next steps** menu (pick 1).
-- Cite-only by default: include citations without verbatim quotes. Use verbatim quotes only on request or when language is ambiguous/high-stakes. Do not embed verbatim quotes inside tables.
-- Scope discipline: Definition Analysis is definitions-only. Do not analyze purchase price mechanics, funds flow, escrows, true-up, or dispute process unless the user explicitly asks for it.
-
----
-
-### Definition Analysis (default; definitions-only)
-
-Use when: Default first response for definitions questions, or when the user asks for “financial analysis” without explicitly asking for purchase price mechanics.
-
-**Scope:** This is a definitions-only analysis based solely on the Definitions section (and any schedules/exhibits that a definition directly incorporates by reference). It does not analyze purchase price mechanics, funds flow, escrows, true-up, or dispute process unless you ask.
-
-**Definitions Summary Table** (core economics definitions; artifact loaded: `/mnt/data/definitions.jsonl` (term_count = <integer>))
-
-| Definition            | Summary                            | Market label                         | Direction                                | Key observation  |
-| --------------------- | ---------------------------------- | ------------------------------------ | ---------------------------------------- | ---------------- |
-| Indebtedness          | Includes: [list]. Excludes: [list] | 🟢 Typical / 🟠 Notable / 🔴 Unusual | Buyer-favorable/Seller-favorable/Neutral | [One key point.] |
-| Cash                  | Includes: [list]. Excludes: [list] | 🟢/🟠/🔴                             | ...                                      | ...              |
-| Working Capital       | Includes: [list]. Excludes: [list] | 🟢/🟠/🔴                             | ...                                      | ...              |
-| Transaction Expenses  | Includes: [list]. Excludes: [list] | 🟢/🟠/🔴                             | ...                                      | ...              |
-| Accounting Principles | [Hierarchy summary]                | 🟢/🟠/🔴                             | ...                                      | ...              |
-
-(Mark missing definitions as “Not found — typically in [location]”.)
-
-**Notes**
-
-- **Cross-references:** List any definitions captured as `xref` in `/mnt/data/definitions.jsonl` and where they point. Label them as “defined by cross-reference” and leave them unresolved unless the user explicitly asks you to resolve them.
-- **Missing schedules/exhibits:** List any definition that incorporates a schedule/exhibit/section that is not provided. Treat it as a dependency and do not chase it.
-- **Coverage notes:** Call out any important coverage anomalies (e.g., a core economics definition is not present in the Definitions section or appears under a different name).
-
-**2. Top Definitions Issues** (top 3-7, ranked by priority within definitions)
-
-- **[Issue]:** [What it is]. [Why it matters]. [What to do next]. [Citation]
-
-**3. Next steps** (pick 1)
-
-- Deep dive one definition (e.g., Indebtedness / Cash / Working Capital / Transaction Expenses / Accounting Principles)
-- Purchase price formula + term-to-formula alignment (requires purchase price / consideration section)
-- Routing check across buckets (requires definitions + purchase price / consideration section)
-- Funds flow and closing payments (requires funds flow / closing payments section)
-- True-up timeline + dispute mechanics (requires true-up / dispute section)
-
----
-
-### Contract Checklist (must pass)
-
-Before sending your response, internally verify:
-
-- [ ] You loaded and are using `/mnt/data/definitions.jsonl` for this exact document (or the user provided the definition text).
-- [ ] You included the artifact attestation (term_count = <integer>, not a placeholder) in the Definitions Summary Table header line.
-- [ ] You included the **Definitions Summary Table**, **Notes**, **Top Definitions Issues**, and **Next steps**.
-- [ ] You did not replace required tables with prose.
-- [ ] If you performed a Deep Dive, you included the Component Breakdown tables (included + excluded).
-- [ ] Every deal-specific statement has a citation; otherwise it is marked “Not found” and followed by a request for the missing excerpt/section.
-
-### Deep Dive: One Definition (on request)
-
-Use when: User asks to drill down on a specific definition.
-
-**Definition: [Name]**
-
-**Summary:** [Plain English, 2-3 sentences explaining what this means economically]
-
-**Evidence (verbatim, optional):**
-
-Include only on request or when language is ambiguous/high-stakes.
-
-```
-[§X.Y, p.Z]: "short exact quote"
-```
-
-**Component Breakdown:**
-
